11. Testing Steps
Complete the AWS setup in Section 5 and create the DUAL contact point from Section 6.
Point the pilot rule at the DUAL contact point and trigger, preview, or wait for it to fire.
Regression check: confirm email recipients receive the same readable message as before.
Confirm the EXAMPLE-PRD-Alerts-JSON topic receives a message and the SQS record body is bare JSON (starts with "{", not an SNS envelope).
Ask the Lambda developer to confirm json.loads succeeds and the mapped alert appears in the internal alert UI with the pilot labels.
Fire a resolved transition and confirm the internal alert updates (not duplicates) via the fingerprint.
Label-less test: temporarily point one alert rule that has no custom labels at the DUAL contact point. Confirm the payload contains only alertname/grafana_folder plus annotations, and the Lambda's fallbacks still produce a sensible internal alert.
Only after steps 3–7 pass, perform the org-wide phase in Section 6.
12. Rollout Plan
Phase 1 — Pilot. DUAL contact point; only the Airflow rule sends JSON. Validate end to end, including the label-less test.
Phase 2 — Org-wide. Add the JSON integration to the shared contact point(s). All ~260 alerts start flowing to the internal system with no per-rule changes. Email behavior is unchanged throughout.
Phase 3 — Label adoption. Teams add the standard label set (Section 8) to their rules over time. Lambda fallbacks and the lookup table shrink as label coverage grows.
